        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 19 at 2:02PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 201 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Sugar Grove to near Oswego. Movement was
north at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glendale Heights, Valley View, Carol Stream, Lily Lake, Kaneville,
Aurora, West Dundee, Wheaton, West Chicago, South Elgin, South
Barrington, Gilberts, Montgomery, Wayne, Dupage Airport, Glen Ellyn,
St. Charles, Sugar Grove, Roselle, Barrington Hills, Sleepy Hollow,
Hoffman Estates, Elk Grove Village, Winfield, and Carpentersville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
